  <h1>PROJECT REPORT - LIBRARY MANAGEMENT SYSTEM</h1>

  <div class="meta">
    <p><strong>Name:</strong> HARIKRISHNAN A</p>
    <p><strong>Roll No:</strong> 24EC029</p>
    <p><strong>Project:</strong> Library Management System</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Repository and Deployment Links</h2>
  <p><strong>Repository:</strong> <a class="link" href="https://github.com/Harikrishnan120A/library-management-system">https://github.com/Harikrishnan120A/library-management-system</a></p>
  <p><strong>Deployed Link:</strong> <a class="link" href="https://harikrishnan120a.github.io/library-management-system/">https://harikrishnan120a.github.io/library-management-system/</a></p>

  <h2>Abstract</h2>
  <p>
    The Library Management System is a Java desktop application developed with Swing GUI and a console fallback mode.
    It automates core library operations such as maintaining book records, issuing and returning books, overdue tracking,
    fine calculation, report generation, and SMS reminders.
  </p>

  <h2>Problem Statement</h2>
  <p>
    Manual library handling is time consuming and error prone. This project addresses that problem by introducing a
    structured software system for reliable data management, validation, and reporting.
  </p>

  <h2>Objectives</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Build a modular object oriented Java application for library operations.</li>
    <li>Provide both graphical and console interfaces.</li>
    <li>Implement business logic with clear separation of concerns.</li>
    <li>Support persistent storage and detailed reporting.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Technology Stack</h2>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Component</th><th>Technology</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Language</td><td>Java 17</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Build Tool</td><td>Maven</td></tr>
    <tr><td>UI</td><td>Java Swing</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Persistence</td><td>Object Serialization (.dat)</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Logging</td><td>java.util.logging</td></tr>
  </table>

